Parvicardium hauniense is a species of mollusc, known as Copenhagen cockle. It is an endemic species to the Baltic Sea.The species was described in 1971 by G. HÃ¸pner Petersen and P. Russell. Its original scientific name was Cardium hauniense.They are around 5 mm in size with a oblique oval shape and have a thin shell. They are found in the Baltic Sea.